rce/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999399233293, \"rank\": 6.007664949710643e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999940511545, \"rank\": 5.948850570222439e-08, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 780, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9956652385896728, \"rank\": 0.0027184028894010094, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the third time\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"24 men\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 675}, {\"ngram\": \"13 women\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"refugee status\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"their host nations\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"12 sports\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Refugee Olympic Team was created as a symbol of hope and to highlight the plight of refugees worldwide.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 793, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999940511545, \"rank\": 5.948850570222439e-08, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 837}, {\"ngram\": \"hope\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"the plight\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"refugees\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 885}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are around 120 million people globally who have been forced to flee their homes due to war, persecution or oppression, a figure that has almost doubled since the Rio Games eight years ago.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 1091, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"around 120 million people\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 932}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"persecution\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1006}, {\"ngram\": \"oppression\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1020}, {\"ngram\": \"a figure\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rio Games\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, that will be reflected by the Refugee Olympic Team fielding its biggest team yet, after 10 athletes competed in Rio in 2016 and 29 at the Covid-delayed Games in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1096, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999399233293, \"rank\": 6.007664949710643e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1133, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999940511545, \"rank\": 5.948850570222439e-08, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999776171338706, \"rank\": 2.238336734928706e-05, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1264, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999878011088289, \"rank\": 1.2198802278499616e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its biggest team\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"10 athletes\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-delayed Games\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, the team includes athletes who have escaped conflicts in Afghanistan, Syria and Iran.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_Republic_of_Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.893298685063674, \"rank\": 0.11944367493339988, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_Republic_of_Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_Republic_of_Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9985707699788708, \"rank\": 0.0014312345570852878, \"text\": \"Syria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\"}, {\"begin\": 1379, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.789746832363044, \"rank\": 0.17445825146511654, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"conflicts\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are also five UK-based members of the Refugee Olympic Team,including boxer Cindy Ngamba, who qualified for the Games by right and has been tipped to win a medal in Paris.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1430, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999940511545, \"rank\": 5.948850570222439e-08, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1467, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cindy_McCain\", \"score\": 0.9999991356170638, \"rank\": 8.30633613146274e-07, \"text\": \"Cindy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cindy_McCain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cindy_McCain\"}, {\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambay_language\", \"score\": 0.6160349135683529, \"rank\": 0.6232846163924596, \"text\": \"Ngamba\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambay_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambay_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1556, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999399233293, \"rank\": 6.007664949710643e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five UK-based members\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"right\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1552}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, the Refugee Olympic Team will have their own emblem and kit, although they will still walk out for the opening ceremony under the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999399233293, \"rank\": 6.007664949710643e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1578, \"end\": 1598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999940511545, \"rank\": 5.948850570222439e-08, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their own emblem\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"kit\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flag\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These athletes also act as a symbol for the 120 million people who have been forced to flee their homes globally,\\\" said Jojo Ferris of the Olympic Refugee Foundation.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee\", \"score\": 0.999999895441766, \"rank\": 1.0455816983317041e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These athletes\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"the 120 million people\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1782}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"Jojo Ferris\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This team is really about shedding a spotlight on that situation.\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This team\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"a spotlight\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"that situation\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While the Olympic Games will draw everyone's attention and we hope reach people's hearts and minds and challenge the often-negative rhetoric presented by the media about refugees, we really want the team to help people understand the positive contribution refugees make to communities and society.\\\"\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone's attention\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"people's hearts\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"minds\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"the often-negative rhetoric\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2120}, {\"ngram\": \"refugees\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2135}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive contribution refugees\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"communities\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2241}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There has been some controversy over an athlete's inclusion in the Refugee Olympic Team ahead of Paris 2024, however.\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2324, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999940511545, \"rank\": 5.948850570222439e-08, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2354, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.145926844920205e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some controversy\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's inclusion\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2316}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the week before the Games, the Cuban Olympic Committee demanded the \\\"immediate exclusion\\\" of an island athlete who was included by as part of the EOR.\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2410, \"end\": 2433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuban_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cuban Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuban_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuban_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2525, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.03754842619471e-18, \"text\": \"EOR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2387}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2404}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"immediate exclusion\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"an island athlete\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2489}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be the first time the team has Cubans on it: Fernando Day\\u00e1n Jorge, a canoeist who won the gold medal in the 1,000-meter canoe sprint in Tokyo 2020 and weightlifter Ramiro Mora, who currently live in the United States and Great Britain, respectively.\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2572, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cubans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999813554, \"rank\": 1.4912519836616588e-11, \"text\": \"Cubans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cubans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cubans\"}, {\"begin\": 2677, \"end\": 2682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999878011088289, \"rank\": 1.2198802278499616e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2705, \"end\": 2711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramiro_de_Maeztu\", \"score\": 0.602790559767012, \"rank\": 0.6358649748900911, \"text\": \"Ramiro\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramiro_de_Maeztu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramiro_de_Maeztu\"}, {\"begin\": 2712, \"end\": 2716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mora_IK\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.0271828889952004e-12, \"text\": \"Mora\", \"types\": [\"Q4498974\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mora_IK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mora_IK\"}, {\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.99987482933